A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the House Study Committee on Telecommunications Services and Programs for the
2 Hearing and Visually Impaired; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Public Service Commission, by an Act of the General Assembly, approved
4 April 11, 1990 (Ga. L. 1990, p. 1118), was directed to establish, implement, administer, and
5 promote a state-wide single provider dual party relay service; and
6 WHEREAS, further Acts of the General Assembly directed the Public Service Commission
7 to provide an audible universal information access service, telecommunications equipment
8 distribution program, and other hearing technology; and
9 WHEREAS, the dual party relay service and other such programs have benefitted the deaf
10 and hard of hearing community and the blind community in Georgia for decades; and
11 WHEREAS, the advent of newer technology over the past 35 years has resulted in a
12 significant reduction in the usage of the dual party relay service in particular; and
13 WHEREAS, the General Assembly, in the interest of fiscal responsibility and good
14 governance, seeks the guidance of the deaf and hard of hearing community and the blind
